'''Adverse''' or '''adverse interest''', in [[law]], is anything that functions contrary to a [[party (law)|party]]'s [[interest]]. This word should not be confused with [[wikt:averse|averse]].
==Adverse possession== In [[property]] law, [[adverse possession]] refers to an interest in real property which is contrary to the in-fact owner of the property. For example, an [[easement]] may permit some amount of access to property which might otherwise constitute a [[trespass]].
