{{For|the technical use in mathematics|Imaginary line (mathematics)}}

In general, an '''imaginary line''' is any sort of [[line (geometry)|geometric line]] that has only an [[abstraction|abstract]] definition and does not physically exist. In fact, is used to identify a [[map]] properly.

As a [[geography|geographical]] concept, an imaginary line may serve as an arbitrary division, such as a [[border]]. It may also be a standardized marking that serves as a measurement or line of reference, such as a [[circle of latitude]] or the [[Prime Meridian]].

