{{Infobox writer <!-- for more information see [[:Template:Infobox writer/doc]] --> |image = | | name = Wilna Adriaanse | caption = | pseudonym = | birth_date = {{birth date|df=yes|1958|3|19}} | birth_place = [[Askham, Northern Cape|Askham]], Kalahari, South Africa | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = Writer | nationality = South African | period = | genre = | subject = | movement = | spouse = Deon Adriaanse | partner = | children = Cobus (Beer) Adriaanse born 20 May 1985, Jaco Adriaanse born 27 October 1987 and Johann Adriaanse born 23 March 1990 | relatives = | influences = | influenced = | signature = | website = {{url | www.wilnaadriaanse.co.za}} }}
'''Wilna Adriaanse''' (born 1958) is a [[South African]] [[Afrikaans]] romantic fiction writer. Her first book, ''Die wingerd sal weer bot'', was published in 2000 under the name Wilmine Burger. Her book, '' 'n Heildronk op liefde'', won the 2003 Lapa Publishers’ Prize for Romance and in 2009 she was awarded the ATKV-Woordveertjie prize for her novel, ''Die boek van Ester''.<ref name="HAT Taal-en-feitegids">HAT Taal-en-feitegids, Pearson, December 2013, {{ISBN|978-1-77578-243-8}}</ref>
Adriaanse was born on 19 March 1958 in the [[Kalahari Desert|Kalahari]], and grew up in [[Worcester, Western Cape|Worcester]]. She matriculated in 1976 from Worcester High School. She earned a BA and BA honours in development administration from the [[University of Stellenbosch]]. In 2011, she completed a master's degree with distinction in Creative Writing at the [[University of Cape Town]]. Her thesis was also published under the title, '''n Klein Lewe'' by Tafelberg.<ref name="nb">{{cite web | url=http://www.nb.co.za/authors/2025 | title=Wilna Adriaanse | publisher=NB Publishers | accessdate=17 January 2016}}</ref> In 1981, she married Deon Adriaanse and settled in Giyani. In 1985 the couple moved to the Western Cape and lived in Durbanville till 2011, whereafter she followed her husband who worked in various locations in Africa. They have three children.
== Works == As Wilna Adriaanse: * ’n Ongewone belegging, Jasmyn, 2001 * Alleenvlug, Jasmyn, 2002 * Die reuk van verlange, Jasmyn, 2003 * Serenade vir ’n nagtegaal, Jasmyn, 2004 * Rebecca, Tafelberg, 2004 * Hande wat heel, Hartklop, 2005 * Met ander woorde, Tafelberg, 2006 * Die boek van Ester, Tafelberg, 2008 * Vier seisoene kind, Tafelberg, 2010 * 'n Klein lewe, Tafelberg, 2012 * Dubbelspel, Tafelberg, 2014 * Eindspel, Tafelberg, 2017 As Wilmine Burger: * Die wingerd sal weer bot, Lapa, 2000 * ’n Heildronk op die liefde, Lapa, 2002 * Liefde is ’n kleur, Lapa, 2002 * Brug van woorde, Lapa, 2004
